title: Resolver cannot find `Timelock` contract
body:

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Clone/Download the Repository
2. Install Dependencies:
`$ npm install`

3. Start Ganache

4. Migrate Smart Contracts
`$ truffle migrate --reset`

## Expected Behavior

everything to compile correctly
## Actual Results

/usr/local/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/4889.bundled.js:21755 throw new Error("Could not find artifacts for " + import_path + " from any sources"); ^

Error: Could not find artifacts for Timelock from any sources at Resolver.require 

## Environment

* Operating System: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
* Ethereum client: ganache v7.3.2
* Truffle version (`truffle version`):v5.5.22 (core: 5.5.22)
* node version (`node --version`):12.22.9
* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.5.1

Hey @jinxlo thanks for opening this issue, it looks like the resolver cannot find the timelock contract. I followed the reproduction steps but I was actually able to get the contracts deployed successfully.

I guess you could check two things?
1. Did you modify the [dappuniversity/governance](https://github.com/dappuniversity/governance) repo after clone? Is the timelock contract actually there?
2. Your npm version _may_ be why this is happening. Try `npm install -g npm@6`, reinstall truffle and ganache, and try again.

Let me know! Good luck.

Hey thank you for your time on helping me solve this issue. 

- [* ] 1. Did you modify the [dappuniversity/governance](https://github.com/dappuniversity/governance) repo after clone? Is the timelock contract actually there?   
- No i did not modify the [dappuniversity/governance](https://github.com/dappuniversity/governance) repo and yes the timelock.sol is contract is there
- [ *] 2. Your npm version may be why this is happening. Try npm install -g npm@6, reinstall truffle and ganache, and try again.
ive updated npm using `npm install -g npm@6`

i've reinstalled everything yet i seem to be having the same issue

Just found the solution the issue there is a confusion of case between contracts/Timelock.sol lower case ell
and contract TimeLock is TimelockController { upper case ell -- from above error truffle is looking for lower case so workaround after compile to uppercase artifact:

mv build/contracts/TimeLock.json build/contracts/Timelock.json

-- or -- before compile, edit contracts/Timelock.sol and change contract TimeLock to Timelock

Hm weird not sure why you had to manually rename it, the lower|upper case should be consistent. It migrated fine for me without changing anything.

Anyway glad it's resolved for you! Cheers.
